To discover countries with similar characteristics, we applied the K-means clustering algorithm (Jain 2010; B Said et al. 2013) to identify similar members among the data points. Let X = {x1,x2,...,xn} be the set of d-dimensional points we seek to cluster into K clusters. In other words, we attempt to assign each xi, i = 1,...,n to a cluster ck, k = 1,...,K. K-means partitions the data such that the squared error between the mean of a cluster and the data points, members of the clusters, is as low as possible. Let mk be the mean of cluster ck. The squared error between a cluster center and its members is defined as:
